[assistant] Built a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.tsx:1` using only local/JLCPCB-imported parts, with `routingDisabled` set on the board and a straightforward breakout layout around the RP2040, USB-C receptacle, power decoupling, reset pull-up, and a GPIO25 status LED.

- Used imported JLCPCB components for the MCU, USB connector, and LED in `imports/RP2040.tsx:1`, `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx:1`, and `imports/XL_1608UGC_06A.tsx:1`
- Exposed the RP2040 on two 1x20 header rows in `index.tsx:9` and `index.tsx:41`, including power, SWD, USB D+/D-, ADC rail, and all GPIOs
- Wired USB-C VBUS, GND, CC pins, shield tabs, and D+/D- into the RP2040 in `index.tsx:155`, then tied the RP2040 supply-related pins to `VBUS` and `V3_3` nets with local decoupling in `index.tsx:172`
- Added a minimal activity LED path from `GPIO25` through `R1` into `D1` in `index.tsx:197`, plus a `RUN` pull-up resistor in `index.tsx:194`
- Assumed a minimal demonstrator breakout rather than a production-ready Pico-class design, so it omits the external QSPI flash, crystal, regulator refinement, and USB protection typically required for a fully bootable RP2040 board

